    "summary": "Being retired since August 2020, I look both forward and back on my professional life. \nLooking forward, I am interested in the use of big data, AI and online teaching in secondary education. \nLooking back, I notice I preferred to be involve in innovations and building schools. \nJust to name a few innovation and developments that I was involved in:\n- introducing the first computers at our school, and later introducing the use of internet and mobile phones\n- experimenting with student centered and autonomous learning\n- experimenting with different ways of testing and working at CITO where we developed the National Exams for Havo Wiskunde-B\n- implementing the \"Tweede Fase\", a major educational and controversial development in HAVO/VWO\n- working in a multicultural environment, also involving discovering the differences in teaching\n- developing an distant learning course in Advanced Math with the European Schools in Karlsruhe and Bergen\n- research on effects of teacher leadership through a Difference in Diferences and a Multilevel regression\n- guiding a fast growing secondary European School through a difficult and turbulent time.",
